Here is a clean, production-ready implementation of **JWT Sign and verify token utility (variant 14)** in Nodejs.

### Explanation
Signs and decodes JSON Web Tokens for API authorization. Specifically, this handles variant case 14.

### Implementation
```javascript
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET || 'secret';
function signToken_v14(payload) {
  return jwt.sign(payload, SECRET, { expiresIn: '1h' });
}
function verifyToken(token) {
  try {
    return jwt.verify(token, SECRET);
  } catch (err) {
    return null;
  }
}
```

